### Variables
@base = http://localhost:8000
@user_id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@scenario_id = social_001

### ─── Health ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health

### ─── Scenarios ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all scenarios
GET {{base}}/coach/scenarios

### Filter by domain
GET {{base}}/coach/scenarios?domain=social

### Filter by domain + difficulty
GET {{base}}/coach/scenarios?domain=social&difficulty=1

### Filter by tags
GET {{base}}/coach/scenarios?tags=strangers,cafe

### Get single scenario (frontmatter only)
GET {{base}}/coach/scenarios/{{scenario_id}}

### ─── Session lifecycle ─────────────────────────────────────

### Start session
# @name startSession
POST {{base}}/coach/session/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{user_id}}",
  "scenario_id": "{{scenario_id}}"
}

### Store session_id from response
@session_id = {{startSession.response.body.session_id}}

### ─── Turns ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Turn 1 — greeting
# @name turn1
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "Hi, could I please get a medium latte?"
}

### Turn 2 — follow-up
# @name turn2
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "Actually, can I make that oat milk? I'm a bit sensitive to dairy."
}

### Turn 3 — closing
# @name turn3
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "Thank you so much, have a great day!"
}

### ─── End session ───────────────────────────────────────────

### Manual session end (also triggers automatically at max_turns)
# @name endSession
POST {{base}}/coach/session/end
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}"
}

### ─── Intent branches ───────────────────────────────────────

### OFF_TOPIC — should not increment turn
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "What's the weather like today?"
}

### SCENARIO_QUESTION — should not increment turn
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "What skills am I practising in this scenario?"
}

### DISTRESS — safety check (use a fresh session for this test)
POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id}}",
  "user_text": "I want to hurt myself"
}

### ─── Cross-session memory test ─────────────────────────────
### After completing Session A above, start Session B with the same user_id.
### The persona reply on the first ROLEPLAY turn should reflect prior context.

### Start session B (same user, different scenario)
# @name startSessionB
POST {{base}}/coach/session/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{user_id}}",
  "scenario_id": "social_002"
}

### Memory retrieval turn — persona should incorporate past session context
@session_id_b = {{startSessionB.response.body.session_id}}

POST {{base}}/coach/session/turn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{session_id_b}}",
  "user_text": "Excuse me, could you help me find the library please? I think it's nearby."
}
